body.pre: This COPASI model was initially developed by Zena Jensvold and later refined by Gordon Bowman and Qusheng Jin. It aims to simulate the energy metabolism of anaerobic methanotrophic archaea (ANME) based on enzyme kinetics and thermodynamics. The model integrates the kinetics and thermodynamics of enzyme reactions to provide a mechanistic understanding of ANME bioenergetics in anaerobic environments.
The volume is set to 1 liter
V_mem = S_mem * mem_thickness S_mem = 4*PI*r^2 mem_thickness = 5e-9 m r = 1e-6 m

Function: to convert charge in mol/l to Vol
delta_phi = m_charge (mol/l) * molal_V
calculated from the dry weight density of 0.242 g/cm^3 and that proteins account for 0.63 of dry weight

MESPT + H2O = FSPT + H+ MESPT, menylh4mpt, CHSPT
KMCH = -0.8059, Km,MESPT = 0.57 mM

MSPT + F420 + H+ = MLSPT + F420H2 MSPT, CH3H4SPT
KMER = -1.3523, Km,MSPT = 0.25 mM, Km,MLSPT = 0.015 mM, Km,F420 = 0.04 mM, Km,F420H2 = 0.012 mM

Biomass reaction is added to acccount for the production of reduced cofactors and metabolite precursor
The stoichiometry of the biomass reaction is estimated from the FBA results: fdred/atp = 0.1799 f420h2/atp = 0.0829 acoa/atp = 0.1018
